{{Nihongo|'''Kaishu Sano'''|佐野 海舟|Sano Kaishū|born 30 December 2000}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{German football updater|FSVMainz}} club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=佐野 海舟：ＦＣ町田ゼルビア：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/player/1617620/#attack |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=9 January 2023 |language=ja}}</ref>

==Career==
After four seasons with [[J2 League]] club [[FC Machida Zelvia|Machida Zelvia]], in December 2022 it was announced that Sano would be joining [[J1 League]] club [[Kashima Antlers]] for the 2023 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=佐野 海舟選手 完全移籍加入のお知らせ {{!}} 鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト |url=https://www.antlers.co.jp/news/release/90727 |website=鹿島アントラーズ オフィシャルサイト {{!}} KASHIMA ANTLERS |access-date=9 January 2023 |language=ja |archive-date=24 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221224010505/https://www.antlers.co.jp/news/release/90727 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Sano appeared as starter at the beginning of the season, appearing in nine of their first ten games. In April, he picked up a knee injury which would leave him out of action for four weeks.<ref>{{cite web |title=MF佐野が全治4週間の負傷【鹿島】：Ｊリーグ.jp |url=https://www.jleague.jp/news/article/24969/ |website=Ｊリーグ.jp（日本プロサッカーリーグ） |access-date=11 April 2023 |language=ja |date=11 April 2023}}</ref>

===Mainz 05===
On 3 July 2024, Sano signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]] on a four-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mainz05.de/news/kaishu-sano-wird-mainzer|trans-title=KAISHU SANO BECOMES MAINZ PLAYER|title=KAISHU SANO WIRD MAINZER|language=German|website=www.mainz05.de|date=3 July 2024|accessdate=3 July 2024}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Sano is the elder brother of fellow professional footballer [[Kodai Sano (footballer)|Kodai Sano]].<ref name=":1">{{cite web |date=13 October 2021 |title=兄とJで戦う夢実現へ。米子北高MF佐野航大が岡山内定! |url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/detail/?343051-343051-fl |accessdate=18 July 2024 |website=ゲキサカ |language=ja}}</ref>

==Controversy==

=== Sexual assault allegations ===
On 17 July 2024, following Sano's transfer to Mainz, it was reported that he was arrested along with two other co-suspects under suspicion of sexually assaulting a woman who had earlier dined with the three men after the woman's friend had left for home.<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 July 2024 |title=サッカー日本代表の佐野海舟容疑者を逮捕…３０代女性に３人で性的暴行の疑い |url=https://www.yomiuri.co.jp/national/20240716-OYT1T50209/ |access-date=16 July 2024 |website=読売新聞オンライン |language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Afp |first=Jiji |date=17 July 2024 |title=Japan soccer player Sano arrested for alleged sexual assault |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2024/07/17/japan/crime-legal/soccer-player-sexual-assault/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240729122451/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2024/07/17/japan/crime-legal/soccer-player-sexual-assault/ |archive-date=29 July 2024 |access-date=29 July 2024 |website=[[The Japan Times]] |language=en}}</ref> He was released on July 29, and prosecutors decided not to indict him on August 8.<ref name="nikkan">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nikkansports.com/m/soccer/japan/news/202505280000463_m.html |title=【日本代表】佐野海舟が初の謝罪会見「賛否もちろん…行動で」昨夏逮捕、勾留期間中に引退も覚悟|website=日刊スポーツ|date=28 May 2025|access-date=2 June 2025}}</ref>

On 5 June 2025, he was selected for the Japan national team for the third round of the 2026 FIFA World Cup Asian qualifiers, scheduled to be held on 10 June, marking his return to the squad.<ref>{{Cite web |title=サッカー日本代表の最新メンバーが発表！ 佐野海舟や渡辺剛らが復帰！ 初招集は佐野航大ら7名に（フットボールチャンネル） |url=https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/c4d678b90ba1424e875c5c4df3d83cbc188f2c28 |website=Yahoo!ニュース |access-date=23 May 2025 |language=ja}}</ref>
At a press conference, head coach Hajime Moriyasu stated, "I have been observing him all along, and after personally reaching out to him, I strongly felt that he is truly remorseful." He continued, "When we consider each team member as part of a family, I asked myself—as a coach facing an individual player—whether we should simply cast someone out of society or the football world for making a mistake. I decided it would be better, as a family, to give him a path to try again."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/865883?page=1 |title=日本代表メンバーに異変「森保監督が"個人的な思い"を語った」佐野海舟の招集だけじゃない"論点"…「驚きの選出」18歳・佐藤龍之介とは何者か？|author=Kei Totsuka|website=Number |date=27 May 2025|access-date=2 June 2025 |language=ja}}</ref>
Sano also held a press conference on the 28th, where he offered a direct apology in his own words.<ref name="nikkan"/>

